      "content": "but those \"small moments\" feel like distractions. like, we're just putting band-aids on a gaping wound of nothingness. even the people i'm connected to... they're just as temporary and accidental as anything else. it doesn't change the fact that everything eventually just fades out and disappears. it makes the struggle feel so pointless.",
